<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8994&amp;p=95281#p95281"><![CDATA[
You can't get data of a special format like SNES nametables without a plugin. Tiled plugins are written in Java, <a href="http://sourceforge.net/apps/mediawiki/tiled/index.php?title=Writing_your_own_plugin" class="postlink">read this</a> - shouldn't be too difficult.<br /><br />I personally don't use general purpose map editors, I prefer to edit large maps as bitmaps with a general purpose graphics editors, then convert it into a tileset and map data with a custom tool (it searches for matching tiles, packs data as needed etc).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4205">Shiru</a> — Sun Jun 10, 2012 1:52 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
